{"abstract":[{"text":"The Core Location framework lets you determine the current location and position of a device. With the new location monitoring service in iOS 4, your app can register for callbacks when the location of the device changes—even when your app isn’t running. Learn details from the experts on notification registration, code execution, geocoding, and further enhancements to determining location.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-115-using-core-location-in-ios-4"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-115-Using-Core-Location-in-iOS-4"},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC10","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Using Core Location in iOS 4"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/115\/","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"references":{"WWDC10.jpeg":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC10.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10.jpeg"}],"alt":null},"WWDC10-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC10-Icon.png","variants":[{"